# shadcn UI

This project uses **only shadcn UI** for UI elements. Do not use custom UI components or other UI libraries for buttons, forms, dialogs, cards, inputs, or similar elements—use shadcn components from `@/components/ui` instead.

## Initialization

If shadcn is not yet initialized in the project, run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding components

To add a specific component, use the add command. Example for the button component:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Replace `button` with the component name you need (e.g. `card`, `dialog`, `input`, `dropdown-menu`). Check [shadcn UI components](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) for the full list.

## Guidelines

- **Use only shadcn UI components** for all interactive and structural UI (buttons, forms, dialogs, cards, inputs, dropdowns, etc.). Do not introduce custom equivalents or other UI libraries.
- Only use custom components if it's a wrapper of a shadcn ui component
- Source components from `@/components/ui`; if a component is missing, add it with `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>` before implementing the feature.
- Use the project's theme tokens (e.g. `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-card`) instead of hardcoded colors like `bg-zinc-*` or `text-black` so theming stays consistent unless it is specified.
- Respect the project's theming: no dark text on dark backgrounds and no light text on light backgrounds.
